  "text": "Furthermore, the correlation of E r with the field decays with the distance from the defect line. we use a number of overrelaxation updates that is smaller than the one for sweeps over the whole lattice. In our numerical experiments we use l i+1 = l i /2 throughout. l 1 is taken as an integer power of 2 and roughly l 1 ≈ ξ. \"replica exchange\" is the swap of configurations as discussed below eq. [CITATION_1] . An important ingredient of the update is the \"translation\".",
